      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1778854175701,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Strategy\n\n- Add empty tables to act as a scaffold.  \n\n-Once these exist, push inserts directly into the tables.  \n\n-For example, if user progress is at 66%, insert it into\nthe table for eventual synchronization. \nThis covers actions like enrollment events and progress\nupdates.  \n-With these tables in place, the data can be rendered to\nthe frontend to display unique dashboards for different\nusers.  \n\n*This approach achieves the required features while\navoiding a massive refactor that would drastically push\nback the completion time.",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Strategy\n\n- Add empty tables to act as a scaffold.  \n\n-Once these exist, push inserts directly into the tables.  \n\n-For example, if user progress is at 66%, insert it into the table for eventual synchronization. \nThis covers actions like enrollment events and progress updates.  \n-With these tables in place, the data can be rendered to the frontend to display unique dashboards for different users.  \n\n*This approach achieves the required features while avoiding a massive refactor that would drastically push back the completion time.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
